OL,3,CHeathrow chief has 'extra loud phone'
OL,4,Cafter sleeping while fire unfolded
OL,6,FHeathrow's boss said he has obtained
OL,7,Fan "extra loud phone" after sleeping
OL,8,Fthrough multiple calls when a decision
OL,9,Fwas made to close the airport because
OL,10,Fof a power outage.
OL,12,FChief executive Thomas Woldbye was
OL,13,Fasleep as his senior staff decided to
OL,14,Fsuspend operations because of a fire
OL,15,Fat a nearby electrical substation.
OL,17,FNo flights operated at the west London
OL,18,Fairport until about 6pm on March 21
OL,19,Fbecause of the blaze which started
OL,20,Flate the previous night.
